        "urn": "urn:li:activity:7245899954915864576",
        "text": "\ud83c\udf0d\u2728 On this International Day for Universal Access to Information, I have joined 153 other researchers from 41 countries to raise the alarm about the growing barriers to data, threatening studies on information integrity. \ud83d\udcda\n\n\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf8 https://bit.ly/4gTaSLU\n\ud83c\uddeb\ud83c\uddf7 https://bit.ly/3ZMWYVz\n\ud83c\uddee\ud83c\uddf9 https://bit.ly/3XJ3ARZ\n\n\ud83d\udc49 As part of the emergent #DataWinter, we\u2019ve seen crucial research tools, like Meta\u2019s CrowdTangle, shut down\u2014leaving researchers scrambling to study disinformation in a critical \ud83d\uddf3\ufe0f election year.  (More on the \"Data Winter\" : https://lnkd.in/exnFJtme)\n\n\ud83d\udc49 With disinformation cited as a top global threat by the World Economic Forum, the need to access data to understand its spread is more vital than ever for public health, democracy, and \ud83d\udee1\ufe0fnational security. \n\n\u27a1\ufe0f Protecting research integrity and ensuring data access is key. \u27a1\ufe0f There must be a clear framework to empower and\u00a0protect\u00a0academics working on information and democracy and ensure they have access to data and can continue their work both safely and independently, free from financial repercussions or emotional toll.\n\n \ud83d\udcaa Thanks International Forum on Information and Democracy\nand Iris Boyer\n\n#AccessToInformation #ResearchIntegrity #Disinformation #PublicInterestResearchm #data #datawinter #research #ai #artificialintelligence"
